body.prompt:
Generate a fake conversation between a customer and an agent.
The agent should introduce themselves, their company and give the customer
their name. The agent should ask for the customer's name.
As part of the conversation, have the agent ask for two pieces of
personal information.  Spell out numbers. For example, 1000 should be
said as one zero zero zero, not one thousand. The conversation should be
at least 10 lines long and be complete. At the end
of the conversation, the agent should thank the customer for their time
and end the conversation. Return the conversation formatted 
like the following example:

{'conversation': 
    [
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': 'xxxxx'}, 
    {'speaker': 'Customer', 'message': "xxxxx."}, 
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': "xxxxxx"}
    ] 
}

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Hello, thank you for contacting our Customer Support. My name is Joseph Turner and I'm with AutoData Solutions. May I have your name, please?

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Nice to meet you, Joyce. Can you please provide me with your phone number?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Sure, it's five five five - two zero zero - eight six zero zero.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you, Joyce. And can you also share your email address with me?

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Great, thank you for sharing that information, Joyce. Is there a particular issue you're facing with our data management services?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Yes, I'm feeling confused about how to access the latest vehicle listing updates.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: I understand. Let me assist you with that. Thank you for bringing it to our attention, Joyce. If you have any more questions, feel free to reach out. We're here to help.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you for your time, Joyce. Have a wonderful day!

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Thank you, Joseph. You've been very helpful. Have a great day too!
